gomodel:SYNGO_1776  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: NCAT2 (Hirano et al., 1992), a rat mAb against alphaN-catenin, was used for\nproduction of other mAbs to this protein. alphaN-catenin selective monoclonal antibody is used in immunoperoxidase and immunogold labelling of cerebellum and cortex. The authors highlighted recruitment to symmetrical pre- and post synaptic adherence apositions that tend to border release site. They also show early developmental recruitment of this symmetrical adhesive structures prior to synaptic vesicle clustering.\n\n2/11/2017 Pim\n- Based on the interaction with N-cadherin shown in Fig.8 the 'extrinsic component...' variant of membrane association was used.. Experimental description: Materials and methods. \"For adult mice those older than 1 mo were used.........The days when the animals were born was regarded as postnatal day 0. The study also used chicken tissue but figures for the annotation involved mouse tissue." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-10" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1776" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

